r a few hours, it finally gets to you.<br>
<br>
In any case I've met so many great roleplayers on Kunark that my entire FV venture was worth it just for this past week or spent there. Even had a regular group of 3 mages and a wizard going there each night. Were we getting the best experience possible for our level range? Heck no. Were we getting filthy rich? Not really. But it sure was fun. Lots of fun in fact. Then I finally made it into the great Sarnak Fortress with a remarkable group (mage, rogue, paladin, cleric...was something straight out of my AD&amp;D days =)) and well that was great fun as well. <br>
<br>
If FV's dying, I fail to see it. It's really what you make of it after all--I'm not going to judge this server's success by the number of raids done, gods killed, or whatever there is to in the &quot;end-game.&quot; I'm having loads of fun developing my character and so are many others according to what I've seen so far.<br>
<br>
