In my world, this server is not dying.  It is THRIVING, and I love it.  I wouldn't even be playing this, anymore, if not for FV opening up.  YMMV, of course.<br>
<br>
If this is a dying world, tho, I guess I will be one of the last to know.  I am not in my 50s or anything, heh, so I don't think my perspective is too goofed up.  I am really having a lot of fun here.  I jes wish everyone else was, too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udreks.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dreks</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/26/02 8:50:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=63>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The server is dying... slowly but surely</span><hr size=1> &lt;&lt;I remember back in 98 there was a brief nano-second when ALL servers were RP.  &gt;&gt;<br>
<br>
Seems like ages ago, does it not?<br>
<br>
&lt;&lt;This is how EQ was MEANT to be.&gt;&gt;<br>
<br>
Finally! I can't even remember the dates of Beta 4, or the opening. Fennin was great role play, the world was new, the game was fun. I remember shouts of &quot;TO ORC HILL LADS!&quot; &quot;CHARGE&quot;! <br>
<br>
Lasted about a month or so LOL.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I have come to the conclusion that if this server is dying, then my adventures in Norrath will die right along with it. My only issue is with the LFG tag, but I have heard from enough higher level folks rebutting the issue that it no longer concerns me. I will work around it. This is a great place with a MUCH more mature population (They should call it the OP server, not the RP server-Old People <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Beyond that, well, lets face it folks. For any of us who have been here since the beginning, ALL of EQ is dying. All the servers have dropped.  Many people, Good people, left because of the hard and fast Vision that Brad held. Brad is gone, new games are out, large numbers have left or migrated, and the attitude of the company has changed dramatically. <br>
<br>
The Pinnacle of the empire has been reached and will never be again. Now VI is doing what they have to in order to stay alive (what many of us warned them about). They had to start listening to the players, and make some drastic changes. I knew the game was finally going to get better when they dropped the Hybrid Penalty. In the world of dumb rules, this was the panicle of success. <br>
<br>
As for now, my hope is that they just leave us alone, and that no unwanted attention is drawn to us.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udreks.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dreks</A> at: 1/26/02 8:57:56 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1>Firiona Vie General Chat</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href="http://www.firionavie.org/">Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.firiona-vie.com/fvchat.html" target="_blank"><h3>Chat Room</a></h3></center> <br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.6.1<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  